Class ASet<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The entry type.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, Iterable<T>, Collection<T>, Set<T>

    public final class ASet<T>
extends LinkedHashSet<T>
    An extension of LinkedHashSet with a convenience append(Object) method.

    Primarily used for testing purposes for quickly creating populated sets.

    // Example: Set<String> s = new ASet<String>().append("foo").append("bar");
